    10	---
    11	
    12	## 3.10.1 How each company approaches System Setup today
    13	
    14	**KBM Hogue** approaches System Setup as the implementation-governance and configuration-foundation layer for the merged-company project. Its BRD articulates the DREAM methodology (Discovery → Realize → Educate → Activate/Naturalize → Maintain), dual executive sponsorship (Sean Scanlon at GSI; Matt Denning at the merged company), program-management leadership (Lorraine Guzman at KBM Hogue), change-management leadership (Kimmy Katsuyoshi), and functional workstream leads from department SMEs. The BRD covers Orion Suite App installation (5 apps), 25+ custom Orion roles with deactivation of standard NetSuite roles, soft-cutover transition strategy, and the structured 8-process-area BRD framework.
    15	
    16	**Pivot Interiors** approaches System Setup as the platform-foundation layer for migration from D365 and HubSpot into NetSuite Orion. Its BRD covers subsidiary structure, integration architecture (HubSpot retained per Marketing §3.01 D-1; Comerica banking per Financial Management §3.08 D-6; SharePoint document management; UKG payroll per Financial Management §3.08), data migration scope, Orion-NetSuite-specific configurations including the merged role taxonomy, and configurations to support its operating cadence.
    17	
    18	Both companies share the same end-state goals: a single NetSuite Orion environment configured for the merged-company operating model, integrated with the platforms that remain (HubSpot for marketing, banking partners, payroll providers, document management), with role-based access supporting the merged-company organizational structure. Where they differ is largely in starting-state context (KBM coming from NetSuite Core; Pivot coming from D365 + HubSpot + multiple specialty platforms) and in the breadth of integration architecture.
    19	
    20	## 3.10.2 Where the two companies align
    21	
    22	**Explicit in both BRDs:**
    23	
    24	- Single NetSuite Orion environment configured for the merged-company operating model
    25	- Custom Orion roles supporting the merged-company organizational structure
    26	- Standard Orion Suite App installation
    27	- Soft-cutover transition strategy (new business in NetSuite while completing legacy work in original systems)
    28	- Change-management approach with named leads
    29	- Document migration to NetSuite File Cabinet and/or integrated document storage
    30	
    31	**KBM-explicit; standard capability carried forward:**
    32	
    33	- DREAM methodology framework (Discovery → Realize → Educate → Activate/Naturalize → Maintain)
    34	- Dual executive sponsorship (Sean Scanlon at GSI; merged-company executive sponsor)
    35	- Functional workstream leads from department SMEs across 8+ process areas
    36	- 6-8 week Discovery phase with validation focus
    37	- 1.5-2 hour discovery sessions with two-part format (capability overview + requirements analysis)
    38	
    39	**Pivot-explicit; standard capability carried forward:**
    40	
    41	- Multi-Design-Center configuration supporting Pivot's existing California locations + KBM's California territories
    42	- HubSpot integration architecture (per Marketing §3.01 D-1)
    43	- D365-to-NetSuite migration tooling and approach
    44	- SharePoint integration consideration (decided in D-3 below)
    45	
    46	These are noted in the merged BRD; configuration proceeds against standard NetSuite Orion implementation patterns and the DREAM methodology.
