   652	## 9. POST-GO-LIVE SUPPORT & LONG-TERM OPTIMIZATION
   653	
   654	### 9.1 Your Business Requirements
   655	
   656	- **REQ-044**: Establish Suite Care program for ongoing support and optimization (ALIGNS)
   657	  - Ongoing support beyond 30-day post-go-live period
   658	  - Managed services option providing dedicated support
   659	  - Bank of hours option enabling flexible support access
   660	  - Continuous platform optimization
   661	
   662	- **REQ-045**: Enable client self-sufficiency on the platform as long-term goal (ALIGNS)
   663	  - NetSuite Champions enable internal support capability
   664	  - Reduction of consultant dependency over time
   665	  - Team becomes self-sufficient managing day-to-day changes
   666	  - Philosophy: "You don't just go live, you thrive"
   667	
   668	### 9.2 Current State Process
   669	
   670	**PROCESS**: Legacy System Support (Current State)  
   671	**TRIGGER**: Question or issue arises; change needed  
   672	**STEPS**:
   673	1. User contacts Core vendor support → potential delays, limited availability
   674	2. User implements workarounds → creates inefficiency
   675	3. User documents needs for future → backlog of enhancements
   676	
   677	**PAIN POINTS**: 
   678	- Legacy system vendor may have limited support resources
   679	- Internal team has become expert in workarounds rather than solution optimization
   680	- Enhancement backlog grows without structured approach
   681	
   682	### 9.3 Orion/NetSuite Solution
   683	
   684	Orion/NetSuite provides multiple post-go-live support options reflecting different client needs and maturity levels. For the first 30 days (included in implementation), intensive support helps team stabilize on platform and builds confidence. For longer-term support, KBM Hoag can select from managed services (dedicated support resources on retainer) or bank of hours (flexible support access), selecting based on expected ongoing support needs.
   685	
   686	The long-term self-sufficiency goal leverages NetSuite Champions identified and trained during implementation. Rather than creating permanent dependency on external consultants, the Champions program builds internal capability. Internal team members become the primary support layer for colleague questions; consultants support Champions on more complex issues. This approach:
   687	- Reduces long-term support costs
   688	- Empowers internal teams to continuously improve platform
   689	- Creates sustainable support model
   690	- Reduces response time (internal colleagues faster than external consultants)
   691	
   692	The "You don't just go live, you thrive" philosophy reflects Orion's commitment to post-implementation success. Implementation is the beginning, not the end. Ongoing optimization, process improvement, and capability enhancement continue post-go-live, with clients increasingly becoming self-sufficient managing those improvements.
   693	
   694	### 9.4 Future State Process
   695	
   696	For 30 days immediately post-go-live, dedicated support team addresses stabilization issues, team questions, and urgent configuration adjustments. After 30 days, KBM Hoag selects Suite Care program (managed services or bank of hours) for ongoing support. Internal NetSuite Champions handle first-line support for colleague questions. When Champions encounter questions requiring expert consultation, they engage Suite Care support. Over time, team capability grows, support needs decrease, and organization becomes increasingly self-sufficient managing platform optimization and changes.
