   714	## 10. TRANSACTION MANAGEMENT & PROJECT NUMBERING
   715	
   716	### 10.1 Your Business Requirements
   717	
   718	- **REQ-046**: Establish consistent project number/naming across Opportunity → Proposal → Sales Order → PO (ALIGNS)
   719	  - Project number remains consistent throughout transaction lifecycle
   720	  - Different transaction types have separate numbering sequences (Opportunity #, Quote #, SO #, PO #)
   721	  - Project number ties all transactions together
   722	  - Enables tracing transaction history for any project
   723	
   724	- **REQ-047**: Enable global search by project, customer name, phone number (ALIGNS)
   725	  - Quick access to any project or customer record
   726	  - Multiple search criteria enabling users to find information efficiently
   727	  - Reduces time spent searching for information
   728	
   729	- **REQ-048**: Configure recent transaction dialog for quick access to last 10-15 items (ALIGNS)
   730	  - Frequently accessed transactions available in recent items dialog
   731	  - Quick access without search when recent item is needed
   732	  - Improves workflow efficiency
   733	
   734	### 10.2 Current State Process
   735	
   736	**PROCESS**: Transaction Access (Current State)  
   737	**TRIGGER**: User needs to access previous order or project  
   738	**STEPS**:
   739	1. User recalls order/transaction number from memory → searches in Core
   740	2. User accesses transaction directly if number recalled → quick if memorized
   741	3. User struggles with search if number not recalled → frustration if unsuccessful
   742	
   743	**PAIN POINTS**: 
   744	- Memorized transaction numbers won't work the same way in NetSuite
   745	- NetSuite transaction numbering different from Core (Opportunity, Quote, SO, PO each have separate sequences)
   746	- User adjustment required to new navigation and search methods
   747	- "Kleenex may be required" adjustment period
   748	
   749	### 10.3 Orion/NetSuite Solution
   750	
   751	Orion/NetSuite provides consistent project numbering across transaction lifecycle—project number visible and usable throughout Opportunity → Quote → Sales Order → Purchase Order → Project flow. While each transaction type has its own sequential numbering (Opportunity-####, Quote-####, SO-####, PO-####), the project number ties them all together, enabling users to trace all transactions related to a specific project.
   752	
   753	Global search capability across project number, customer name, and phone number enables users to find transactions without memorizing specific transaction numbers. This is more intuitive and less error-prone than trying to remember order numbers. The search by phone number is particularly useful for order entry staff receiving calls from customers—they can quickly locate customer record by phone without needing customer number.
   754	
   755	Recent transaction dialog (last 10-15 items) provides frequently accessed transactions without requiring search. This small usability feature significantly improves workflow for data entry staff repeatedly accessing same transactions.
   756	
   757	The adjustment from memorized order numbers to search-based navigation is acknowledged as a temporary challenge ("Kleenex may be required"), but is quickly overcome as users become familiar with new approach. The project number consistency provides continuity, helping users understand that while the transaction numbers changed, the project identification remains consistent.
   758	
   759	### 10.4 Future State Process
   760	
   761	Users will access transactions either through global search (by project, customer, or phone) or through recent transaction dialog if the transaction was recently accessed. Project number will be visible on all related transactions (opportunity, quote, sales order, PO), enabling users to understand relationship between transactions even with different transaction numbers. Over time, users become familiar with new search approach and transaction numbering, making it natural and efficient.
   762	
