_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1751:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:590:    18	**Pivot** runs a structured CRM out of HubSpot for opportunity management, with downstream quoting and invoicing already in NetSuite (and migrating from D365). Forecasting is exported monthly from HubSpot to Excel, weighted manually, and pivoted for executive review — accurate but lagging by days or weeks. RFPs are tracked separately in Monday.com. Pivot's organization is structured around four divisions (Enterprise, Venture, Public, Construction Solutions) with a hierarchy of executive → SVP/GM → sales operations → designers/reps. Pivot's pain point is *real-time visibility and integration*; their data discipline is already good, but the round trip through Excel costs them speed and the disconnect between CRM and downstream systems costs them margin visibility.
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1771:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:774:   202	| Posture | Minimal use (≤6 campaigns/year); MailChimp pain points; willing to use NetSuite native (120K emails/month included) for occasional campaigns | HubSpot retained for marketing campaigns and lead capture (bidirectional sync proposed in BRD) |
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1772:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:776:   204	**What it means.** Pivot wants to keep HubSpot as the marketing platform with NetSuite Orion as the CRM/opportunity system of record. KBM doesn't care strongly about the marketing tool — they just want to stop fighting MailChimp.
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1773:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:778:   206	**Recommendation.** Retain HubSpot for marketing per Pivot's preference. Configure bidirectional HubSpot ↔ NetSuite Orion sync (Pivot's spec) so KBM-side contacts and leads also flow through HubSpot for the merged company. KBM's email marketing requirement is satisfied implicitly.
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1774:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:780:   208	**Decision for Matt.** Confirm: HubSpot retained for marketing, integrated with Orion CRM. *Default: yes.*
