_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1846:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1306:125:Pivot Interiors operates a complex, relationship\-driven sales organization spanning Enterprise, Venture, Public, and Construction Solutions segments across California\. The company currently relies on HubSpot for pipeline forecasting and opportunity tracking while NetSuite handles downstream quoting, ordering, and financial processes\. Manual forecasting, fragmented stakeholder visibility, and disconnected analytics limit leadership's ability to manage pipeline health, cross\-sell opportunities, and margin discipline in real time\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1848:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1316:173:HubSpot is the system of record for opportunity management and forecasting\. Sales operations exports the pipeline monthly, applies weighted probabilities in Excel, and produces a pivot table for executive review\. Forecast data is manually fed into downstream leadership reports, delaying insight by days or weeks\. Opportunity and lead creation relies on HubSpot quick forms with minimal required fields, enabling reps to enter deals in under two minutes and progressively enrich data later\. Mobile usability is critical because many reps work from job sites\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1849:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1317:177:NetSuite Orion replaces HubSpot as the CRM system of record, delivering native opportunity management with configurable probability percentages that mirror Pivot's four\-stage methodology\. Weighted pipeline calculations update in real time, driving dashboards and saved searches sliced by division, SVP, and rep\. Quick\-add opportunity and lead forms leverage role\-based defaults and required field logic to match Pivot's "speed first, enrich later" workflow, including full mobile parity through the NetSuite mobile app\. This ensures rapid adoption while improving data quality and governance\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1850:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1325:227:HubSpot allows only one primary company per opportunity\. Secondary stakeholders like architects, general contractors, and project managers are tracked manually in notes or spreadsheets, limiting visibility into cross\-sell potential\. Influencer data is inconsistently captured because there are no structured reminders, undermining win/loss analysis\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1853:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1333:277:Reps identify Construction Solutions’ involvement via a field in HubSpot, but no automated alert notifies the Construction Solutions team\. Nicholas' team relies on manual report monitoring, causing missed revenue opportunities\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1865:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1351:363:Currently, HubSpot does not capture GP\. Only the deal amount is entered at the opportunity stage\. No gross profit fields or margin calculations are being tracked within HubSpot today\.
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1868:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1364:449:Annual goals live in HubSpot, while the 2\.5× multiplier is calculated manually in 15:5 reviews and PowerBI\. Reps lack real\-time visibility into multiplier status\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1869:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1369:491:Activity logging in HubSpot is enforced manually for new hires and underperformers\. Experienced reps have flexibility, and there is limited visibility into coaching effectiveness\. 
_Unification/working/codex-run-v2.log:1870:_Unification/working/codex-run.log:1373:531:1. HubSpot Integration: Bi\-directional sync for lead capture, marketing campaign membership, and opportunity creation\. 
